solution: ```class Solution {
    public int alternateDigitSum(int n) {
        int sum = 0, sign = 1;
        while (n > 0) {
            sum += sign * (n % 10);
            n /= 10;
            sign *= -1;
        }
        return (sum * -sign) / 2;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Process digits from least-significant to most-significant, flipping the sign each step. After the loop, the sign is one step too far, so reverse the final flip and divide by 2 to correct the alternating pattern starting with + on the most-significant digit.

